strongest_concepts: Basic definitions in biology (cells, fermentation); Simple calculations and conversions (decimals to fractions); Application of formulas (Newton's second law)
weakest_concepts: Applying formulas related to pressure; Understanding wave properties (wavelength, frequency); Dalton's Atomic Theory
dominant_mistake_pattern: The student frequently makes mistakes on hard-difficulty conceptual questions, often misinterpreting definitions or relationships between concepts. Calculation errors are also apparent.
llm_summary: The student performs well on easy and medium-difficulty questions, particularly those involving straightforward calculations or definitions. However, they struggle with more complex conceptual questions and application of formulas in physics and chemistry.

strongest_concepts: Basic recall questions; Elementary mathematics; Fermentation; Micro-organism habitat
weakest_concepts: Atomic Theory; Cell structures; Wave properties; Force and Motion; Algebraic manipulations; Decoding; Family relations; Fractions and decimals
dominant_mistake_pattern: The student frequently selects incorrect answers in hard questions, often appearing to guess or misapply concepts learned. Conceptual errors outweigh calculation errors.
llm_summary: The student shows proficiency with easy recall questions, but struggles with medium and hard difficulty questions, particularly those involving abstract concepts and multi-step problem-solving. There is a lack of consistent application of fundamental principles across various topics.
